Delancey Street, at, adjoining and east of the N.E. corner of Forsyth Street.
About 1914.

Joseph P. Day.

(1) Delancey Street, at, adjoining and west of the N.W. corner of Forsyth Street. Also shown, is Forsyth Street, west side, north from Delancey, to and including East Houston Streets. These buildings will be completely demolished to form a portion of the site of the Sarah Delano Roosevelt Park.

July 18, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.

(2) The same, at a later date.

P. L. Sperr.
